{"action": "input", "code": "def find_small_pattern(big_pattern: np.ndarray, small_patterns: Dict[int, np.ndarray], double_small_patterns: Dict[int, np.ndarray]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes a big pattern, a dictionary of small patterns, and a dictionary of double small patterns and returns\n    the small pattern that corresponds to the double small pattern containing the big pattern.\n    \n    Args:\n    big_pattern: A numpy array representing the big pattern which contains 2x2 grids of the input patterns.\n    small_patterns: A dictionary where each key is a color and the corresponding value is a numpy array representing the pattern\n    of that color in the small 2x2 grids of the big pattern.\n    double_small_patterns: A dictionary where each key is a color and the corresponding value is a numpy array representing the pattern\n    of that color in the small 2x2 grids of the input patterns.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the pattern of the color in the small 2x2 grids of the big pattern.\n    \"\"\"\n    for color, double_small_pattern in double_small_patterns.items():\n        for i in range(2):\n            for j in range(2):\n                if np.array_equal(double_small_pattern[i], big_pattern):\n                    return small_patterns[color]\n    return None\ndef replace_pixel_with_2x2_grid(patterns: Dict[int, np.ndarray]) -> Dict[int, np.ndarray]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes a dictionary of color patterns and returns a dictionary where each key is a color\n    and the corresponding value is a numpy array representing the pattern of that color in the small 2x2 grids.\n    \n    Args:\n    patterns: A dictionary where each key is a color and the corresponding value is a numpy array representing the pattern\n    of that color in the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A dictionary where each key is a color and the corresponding value is a numpy array representing the pattern\n    of that color in the small 2x2 grids.\n    \"\"\"\n    small_patterns = {}\n    for color, pattern in patterns.items():\n        small_pattern = np.zeros((2,) + pattern.shape)\n        for i in range(2):\n            for j in range(2):\n                small_pattern[i] = pattern\n        small_patterns[color] = small_pattern\n    return small_patterns\ndef get_other_colors(input_grid: np.ndarray, background_color: int) -> List[int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes an input grid and the background color and returns a list of colors that appear in the grid\n    except the background color.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    background_color: An integer representing the background color.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A list of integers representing the colors that appear in the grid except the background color.\n    \"\"\"\n    unique_colors = np.unique(input_grid)\n    other_colors = [color for color in unique_colors if color != background_color]\n    return other_colors\ndef complete_pattern(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    background_color = get_background_color(input_grid)\n    colors = get_other_colors(input_grid, background_color)\n    patterns = get_color_patterns(input_grid, colors)\n    big_pattern = get_2x2_pattern(patterns)\n    small_patterns = get_small_patterns(patterns, big_pattern)\n    double_small_patterns = replace_pixel_with_2x2_grid(small_patterns)\n    result_pattern = find_small_pattern(big_pattern, small_patterns, double_small_patterns)\n    output_grid = _hole7(result_pattern, background_color)\n    return output_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    background_color = get_background_color(input_grid)\n    colors = get_other_colors(input_grid, background_color)\n    patterns = get_color_patterns(input_grid, colors)\n    big_pattern = get_2x2_pattern(patterns)\n    small_patterns = get_small_patterns(patterns, big_pattern)\n    double_small_patterns = replace_pixel_with_2x2_grid(small_patte