rs and returns a dictionary where each key is a color\n    and the corresponding value is a numpy array representing the pattern of that color in the input grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    colors: A list of integers representing the colors to get the patterns for.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A dictionary where each key is a color and the corresponding value is a numpy array representing the pattern\n    of that color in the input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    color_patterns = {}\n    for color in colors:\n        color_pattern = np.zeros_like(input_grid)\n        color_pattern[input_grid == color] = 1\n        color_patterns[color] = color_pattern\n    return color_patterns\ndef get_2x2_pattern(patterns: Dict[int, np.ndarray]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes a dictionary of color patterns and returns a numpy array representing the pattern\n    which contains 2x2 grids in the input patterns.\n    \n    Args:\n    patterns: A dictionary where each key is a color and the corresponding value is a numpy array representing the pattern\n    of that color in the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the pattern which contains 2x2 grids in the input patterns.\n    \"\"\"\n    pattern_shape = next(iter(patterns.values())).shape\n    big_pattern = np.zeros((2, 2) + pattern_shape)\n    for i in range(2):\n        for j in range(2):\n            big_pattern[i, j] = patterns[next(iter(patterns))].copy()\n    return big_pattern", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n  background_color = `the color which has most pixels`(input_grid)\n  colors = `other colors appear in the picture except background_color`(input_grid, background_color)\n  patterns = `get the pattern of each color`(input_grid, colors)\n  big_pattern = `get the pattern which contains 2*2 grids in patterns`(patterns)\n  small_patterns = `patterns except the big_pattern`(patterns, big_pattern)\n  double_sm